Pearl Thusi attends the 2018 Global Citizen Festival: Be The Generation in Central Park on September 29, 2018 in New York City. JOHANNESBURG - Actress and media personality Pearl Thusi led the star-studded arrivals at the Queen Sono premiere in Johannesburg on Thursday night. Thusi plays the lead character in the series which was directed by South African comedian Kagiso Lediga. Queen Sono: SA's first Netflix original series Several stars including Cassper Nyovest, Thando Thabethe and Sho Madjozi attended the premiere which was held at the Joburg Theatre. Queen Sono, Netflix's first original African series is scheduled for release on Friday, February 28.